properties.NAME: 97 Nyssa sylvatica ✘
properties.ADRESS1: Nyssa sylvatica, commonly known as Tupelo, Black gum, sour gum, is a medium-sized deciduous tree native to eastern North America from the coastal Northeast USA and southern Ontario south to central Florida and eastern Texas, as well as Mexico. ✘

properties.NAME: 98 Podocarpus elatus
properties.ADRESS1: Podocarpus elatus, known as the plum pine, the brown pine or the Illawarra plum is a species of Podocarpus endemic to the east coast of Australia, in eastern New South Wales and eastern Queensland. It is a medium to large evergreen tree growing to 30–36 m tall with a trunk up to 1.5 m diameter.

properties.NAME: 99 Dombeya cacuminum
properties.ADRESS1: We have a tree from Madagascar described in some books as one of the most outstanding flowering trees of the world. It is just coming into flower here. The tree is called Dombeya cacuminum, commonly called overseas “The Strawberry Snowball Tree” The tree is named after Joseph Dombey an 18th century French botanist, doctor and explorer. The genus is included in the Byttneriaceae family – a recent division of the Sterculiaceae family. The cocoa tree belongs in this family.
